{
  "texts": [
    "The convolution blocks convert the inputs into token embeddingsV 1 b ∈ R H 4 × W 4 ×C1, V 2 b ∈ R H 8 × W 8 ×C2, V 3 b ∈ R H 16 × W 16 ×C3, etc.",
    "Meanwhile, all scale features are transformed into the same channel dimension and concatenated together channel-wisely.",
    "The feature extraction process can be written asV 1 b = ConvBlock 1 (I 1),(4)V i b = ConvBlock i (V i-1 b), i = 2,..., m,(5)V b = Concat V 1 b, V 2 b,...V m b,(6)where the I 1 represents the first scale input.",
    "The multiscale fused visual features encompass information of multigranularity, enabling the capture of both broad semantics and intricate information.",
    "After extracting visual features using ViT and CNN, multilayer and multi-scale features are concatenated channel-wisely."
  ]
}